I used to have a series on my Tumblr called “In Medias Res” which means into the middle of things in Latin. It’s typically a literary term for a work that begins its narrative mid plot. For me, it meant photographing someone as I caught up with them. Bringing it back here sporadically to catalogue NY style. @alex_delany #InMediasResbyFeni

I think this is the year I bring shooting street style back into my life more consistently. I want to highlight people and things that might not get typical press. To kick things off, I’ve started a Substack and my first post is a quick interview with @sameersadhu and @samerms, who hosted a closet sale at @leisure__centre this past weekend. The link to the post is in my story and bio.

Hoping to bring In Medias Res back more frequently through my Substack. I’ll do informal interviews with people you wouldn’t normally see covered by traditional fashion media. I’ve always loved reading more about real, stylish people, and seeing their everyday outfits. First up is the all-time great @nickelcobalt. We only did a couple of outfits since I’ve already done #FiveFitsWith with him.
After a brief hiatus, #FiveFitsWith is back for the fall starting with @mitchsjackson. Read our interview, and see the rest of the photos, on @esquire’s site.
A bit of street style from last week, mostly outside of the @4sdesigns_ presentation. See some additional photos and a reflection from me on my Substack. The link can be found in my bio.

#FiveFitsWith @e.m.reitz. Hoping to bring many more menswear-adjacent women to the series, but Erin and her shirts are in a league of their own. We touch on a host of topics, like how a chance encounter at a dive bar brought her to the fashion design world, and why she’s ready to ditch the clothing term “boyfriend” and give women their own timeless silhouettes. Read our interview, and see the rest of the photos, on @esquire’s site.

2.5 months with Desmond. 🖤

Street style photographed for the @spr.ezza x @huckberry pop-up this past weekend. I really like what @claytonchambrs is doing with Sprezza and it’s been fun to document some milestones for him. This felt a bit like the 2010’s Tumblr era. Good product and a sense of community.

#FiveFitsWith @buckmeek. Aside from loving his solo project, as well as @bigthiefmusic, I always thought Buck had really unique style and would be an interesting fit for this column. Read our interview, and see the rest of the photos, on @esquire’s site.
#FiveFitsWith @terance of the @laclippers. Read our interview, and see the rest of the photos, on @esquire’s site.
Last #FiveFitsWith of the year with @rackkwall of the @nygiants. Hoping to see him back on the field soon. Read our interview, and see the rest of the photos, on @esquire’s site.

Every wedding I’ve shot is an honor, but it’s extra special when I can work with friends; particularly ones I’ve known for the entire duration of their relationship. This was also my first one bringing @mitchellwojcik on to shoot with me, a guy whose work I’ve admired for many years. I loved this day and wedding immensely.

One of the freshest dudes I know, @kamauhosten, photographed last month on the Upper East Side wearing an impeccable @tailorcaid coat made with the same fabric worn by Daniel Day Lewis in “Phantom Thread.”

#FiveFitsWith Brendon Babenzien, founder of @noahclothing and creative director of @jcrewmens. I had a really great conversation with Brendon about his time at Supreme, his role at J.Crew, the pitfalls of social media and shallow consumerism, and plenty of other topics. Read our interview, and see the rest of the photos, on @esquire’s site.
